title: B.B. King - Live at Jazz Summit in Wiesen, Austria 1984 (SBD) [F
description:
B.B.KING & BAND
Live at Jazz Summit in Wiesen, Austria, Europe on July 8, 1984

Unofficial Soundboard Recording - EXCELLENT sound quality
(almost flawless - only a small break in the recording of Caledonia - so it's divided in two parts)


TRACKS:

CD 1
1. Introduction Jam > Every Day I have the Blues
2. Paying The Cost To Be The Boss
3. Sweet Little Angel
4. Instrumental
5. Rock Me Baby
6. Instrumental
7. Caledonia Part I
8. Caledonia Part II
9. When It All Comes Down (I'll Still Be Around)
10. Instrumental Jam
11. I Just Can't Leave Your Love Alone

CD 2:
1. Evil Gal Blues (Aretha Franklin cover)
2. How Blue Can You Get?
3. The Thrill is Gone


Lineup:

B.B.King -  guitar, vocals
Edgar Synegal - tenor sax
James Bolden - trumpet
Leon Warren - guitar
Joseph Carrier - piano, organ
Russell Jackson - bass
Calep Emphrey - drums
Debra Boston - vocals (lead vocals on I Just Can't Leave Your Love Alone & Evil Gal Blues)
